module:
development.folder="dvlp">
module, class, library, set theory, activity, relationship, structure, process plant
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to record:
classes of activity, with their whole-part, connection and involvement relationships; and
set theory relationships, such as subset, union and intersection, between these classes.
the existence of a class of activity;
a mapping between one class of activity and another that indicates the nature of a whole-part relationship between two individual activities;
A mapping between classes of activity is a class that has relationships between individual activities as members.
a mapping between one class of activity and another that indicates the nature of a connection relationship between two individual activities;
a mapping between a class of activity and a class that indicates the nature of an involvement in an activity;
set theory relationships, such as subset, union and intersection, between classes of activity and between mappings.
individual activity; Individual activity is within the scope of the Individual_activity application module.
membership of a class of activity. Membership of a class of activity is within the scope of the Activity_structure_and_classification application module.
